<HEAD>Interior Delaying Leases for Lack of Interest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Interior Department said today it will
delay an offering of oil and gas leases in federal waters off
Florida, Georgia and North and South Carolina because of limited
industry interest.
   Robert Kallman, director of the department's Minerals Management
Service, said environmental studies of the area would continue and
the government would issue another request for expessions of
drilling interest this fall.
   The lease auction, originally scheduled for October 1990, now is
planned for some time early in 1992.
   Last September, the department asked for nominations of specific
tracts to be offered in the 75-million acre area off the coast of
the four states.
