<HEAD>Four Committee Members Unseated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reporters for magazines and other periodical
publications unseated four members of the committee that accredits
journalists who work out of the Periodical Press Gallery in Congress.
   The mail balloting, whose results were announced Friday, was led
by Douglas Harbrecht of McGraw-Hill publications with 439 votes.
   Other winners: Hays Gorey, Time, Inc., 419 votes; Mark Allen
Kellner, Fairchild Publications, 378; Stan Zimmerman, Pasha
Publications, 361; Patrick M. Clawson, Radio &amp; Records, 359; Arthur
Brodsky, Warren Publishing, 357, and Rebecca Pearl, BNA
Publications, 355.
   Harbrecht, Gorey and Ms. Pearl are incumbents.
   The defeated candidates: Andy Plattner, U.S. News &amp; World Report;
Rich Maze, Times Journal Publications; Richard Cohen, National
Journal, and Ken Dalecki, Washington Kiplinger Editors.
   The major issue in the campaign was a new directive by the panel
_ officially the Executive Committee of the Periodical
Correspondents Association _ requiring stricter disclosure of
outside income.
