<HEAD>Police Seek US Policeman Who May Have Taken Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWCASTLE UPON TYNE, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Friday they are
watching docks and airports for a British-born policeman from
California who may have entered his estranged wife's home and taken
their two young children.
   A statement from the Northumbria police force identified the man
as Malcolm Lowery, 30, and said he was a policeman in Santa Ana,
Calif. It said a 20-year-old American woman friend named Kathy
Marsh, no hometown given, was believed to be traveling with him.
