<FIRST>r i AM-Swiss-SovietSpy     02-03 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Swiss-Soviet Spy,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Swiss Expel Soviet Trade Official For Spying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A member of the Soviet trade mission in
the Swiss capital has been expelled for spying, the Federal
Prosecutor's Office said Friday.
   The Foreign Ministry protested to the Soviet Embassy over illegal
activities by the diplomat, who had sought access to secret military
and other advanced technology in Switzerland since 1987, the office
said.
   The Soviet official, whose name and position were not published,
built contacts with Swiss companies and individuals with the aim of
gaining access to Western high technology and placing agents in
industries targeted by Moscow, the prosecutor's office statement
said.
   The diplomat has been recalled by Moscow and was barred from
re-entering Switzerland, the statement said.
   The last Soviet spy case in Switzerland was uncovered in May.
Communist agents account for about two thirds of all spies expelled
from Switzerland since 1970. Most cases in the 1980s have involved
economic espionage.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
