<HEAD>Belgium Ups Key Interest Rate Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Belgium's central bank slightly raised a
key interest rate Friday for the second time in as many days.
   The National Bank increased the rate on three-month treasury
bills to 7.85 from 7.75 percent. The rate was brought to 7.75
percent from 7.7 percent on Thrusday.
   The increase was the fourth so far this year and reflected the
general uptrend in Belgian and international rates.
