<FIRST>r f PM-ConsumerRecalls     02-03 0333</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Consumer Recalls,0344</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: The commission's hotline is 1-800-638-2772</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Manufacturers and importers are recalling some
lawn mowers, dolls, toy boats, baby rattles and toy kitchens,
according to the Consumer Product Safety Commission.
   Here is a rundown of several commission announcements Thursday:
   _Lawn mowers: Toro Co. of Minneapolis is recalling 19,000
rear-engine riding mowers made between 1972 and 1979 because of the
danger that users can sit on or fall on rotating starter parts.
Mowers made for the 1973 model year can be started in gear, and
1972-1976 mowers may be accidentally bumped into gear. The company
is paying a fine of $75,000 to settle charges of violating defect
reporting requirements of federal law, charges it denies.
   Model numbers 56575, 56025, 56030, 56027, 56033 and 56044 may be
affected.
   _Dolls: Rite-Aide Corp. of Harrisburg, Pa., is recalling about
1,000 ``L'il Bonnie 'n Beth'' dolls of Style No. 303 because some of
the dolls' arms and legs may come off and choke young children. The
dolls are seated in a pull-toy car bearing the word ``LOVEE'' on
each wheel and front and rear license plates.
   _Rattles: M. Adler's Son, Inc. of Brooklyn, N.Y., is recalling
93,000 plastic flower-shaped rattles, No. M6588, because they may
break, with the pieces posing a choking hazard.
   _Boats: Target Stores of Minneapolis is recalling about 1,300
``Press'n Roll Boats'' of Model No. 2311 because the smokestack of
the toy vessel may break off and choke young children.
   _Kitchens: Amloid Co. of Saddle Brook, N.J., is recalling 75,000
``Cook N Clean Kitchen'' small plastic toy kitchen components
because parts could come off and choke young children.
   The commission said parents should take the dolls, rattles and
boats away from children, returning them for refunds _ rattles and
kitchens to the store where purchased, dolls to the nearest Rite-Aid
store and boats to the nearest Target store.
   Mower owners who have not received a recall notice should contact
the nearest Toro Service dealer.
   The commission's hotline is 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
